messages.content: You are tasked with creating a structured output from the provided user message.

- Full path: /v1/posts

- all methods acceptable: false

- HEAD: false
- POST: true
- OPTIONS: false
- TRACE: false
- GET: false
- PUT: false
- DELETE: false
- PATCH: false

Explanation:
- In routes/api.php there is a Route::prefix('v1')->group(...). Inside that group the PostController::store method is registered via Route::apiResource('posts', PostController::class)->only(['update', 'store', 'destroy']); The apiResource mapping registers the "store" action as a POST request to the resource base path, i.e. POST /v1/posts. Therefore POST is accepted for the PostController@store endpoint and the full path is /v1/posts.
- The other HTTP verbs are not declared for this store action in the routes shown. PUT/PATCH/DELETE routes exist for /v1/posts/{post} (update/destroy) but those are different endpoints (they target the {post} resource). GET for /v1/posts is registered elsewhere in the file (index action) and maps to the same path but to PostController@index, not to the store action â€” therefore GET is not acceptable for the store action.
- I did not assume framework implicit behaviors (such as automatic HEAD handling or automatic OPTIONS responses); only routes explicitly declared in the provided code were considered.
